From: JP Hein <jp@jphein.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Mar 2026 12:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] media: uvcvideo: add quirks for Razer Kiyo Pro webcam

The Razer Kiyo Pro (1532:0e05) is a USB 3.0 webcam with firmware that
has two issues that can cascade into full xHCI host controller failure:

1. When the device enters USB autosuspend and then resumes, it can fail
   to reinitialize its UVC endpoints correctly, producing SET_CUR probe
   control errors (-32, EPIPE). The stalled endpoint then triggers an
   xHCI stop-endpoint command timeout, which causes the kernel to
   declare the entire host controller dead.

2. The device's reset-resume path is similarly fragile — a USB reset
   during resume can leave the device in an inconsistent state where
   subsequent control transfers hang, again leading to xHCI controller
   death.

Apply UVC_QUIRK_DISABLE_AUTOSUSPEND to prevent the device from entering
USB autosuspend states that trigger the firmware bug, and
UVC_QUIRK_NO_RESET_RESUME to avoid the problematic reset-during-resume
path. Together, these prevent the conditions that lead to the xHCI
cascade failure.

This is the same approach used for Logitech Rally Bar devices
(NO_RESET_RESUME) and Actions Microelectronics / Insta360 cameras
(DISABLE_AUTOSUSPEND).

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Link: https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/linux/+bug/2061177
Signed-off-by: JP Hein <jp@jphein.com>
---
 drivers/media/usb/uvc/uvc_driver.c | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/usb/uvc/uvc_driver.c b/drivers/media/usb/uvc/uvc_driver.c
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/drivers/media/usb/uvc/uvc_driver.c
+++ b/drivers/media/usb/uvc/uvc_driver.c
@@ -3125,6 +3125,17 @@ static const struct usb_device_id uvc_ids[] = {
 	  .bInterfaceProtocol	= 0,
 	  .driver_info		= (kernel_ulong_t)&uvc_quirk_probe_minmax },

+	/* Razer Kiyo Pro */
+	{ .match_flags		= USB_DEVICE_ID_MATCH_DEVICE
+				| USB_DEVICE_ID_MATCH_INT_INFO,
+	  .idVendor		= 0x1532,
+	  .idProduct		= 0x0e05,
+	  .bInterfaceClass	= USB_CLASS_VIDEO,
+	  .bInterfaceSubClass	= 1,
+	  .bInterfaceProtocol	= 0,
+	  .driver_info		= UVC_INFO_QUIRK(UVC_QUIRK_DISABLE_AUTOSUSPEND
+					| UVC_QUIRK_NO_RESET_RESUME) },
+
 	/* Oculus VR Positional Tracker DK2 */
 	{ .match_flags		= USB_DEVICE_ID_MATCH_DEVICE
 				| USB_DEVICE_ID_MATCH_INT_INFO,
--
2.43.0
